<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,757,1069]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,757,782]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae 
<number box="[397,410,757,781]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="9.0">9</number>
-segmented, segments III–IV with circumpolar sensoria at apex, with one or more rows of sensorial pores; III with two basal constrictions. Head wider than long, without long setae; ocellar setae I present or absent. Pronotum with no long setae (
<figureCitation box="[600,687,829,853]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[210,1363,195,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[210,1365,195,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 20. Brazilian Heterothrips. H. pedicellatus sp. n. female 11 – 20: 11. Dorsal view; 12. Mesonotum and metanotum; 13. Head; 14. Pronotum; 15. Antennal segments II – IV; 16. A ntenna; 17. Abdominal tergites IV – VI; 18. Abdominal sternites IV – VI; 19. Abdominal tergites I – III; 20. Fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280413/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[656,687,829,853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
); metanotum covered with microtrichia, usually with concentric sculpture but sometimes almost forming a triangle medially (
<figureCitation box="[837,920,865,889]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[210,1363,195,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[210,1365,195,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 20. Brazilian Heterothrips. H. pedicellatus sp. n. female 11 – 20: 11. Dorsal view; 12. Mesonotum and metanotum; 13. Head; 14. Pronotum; 15. Antennal segments II – IV; 16. A ntenna; 17. Abdominal tergites IV – VI; 18. Abdominal sternites IV – VI; 19. Abdominal tergites I – III; 20. Fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280413/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[889,920,865,889]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Fore wing slender, wider at base, both veins with complete rows of setae (
<figureCitation box="[493,580,901,925]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[210,1363,195,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[210,1365,195,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 20. Brazilian Heterothrips. H. pedicellatus sp. n. female 11 – 20: 11. Dorsal view; 12. Mesonotum and metanotum; 13. Head; 14. Pronotum; 15. Antennal segments II – IV; 16. A ntenna; 17. Abdominal tergites IV – VI; 18. Abdominal sternites IV – VI; 19. Abdominal tergites I – III; 20. Fore wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280413/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[548,580,901,925]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergites laterally covered with microtrichia, with posteromarginal fringe of independent microtrichia (Fig. 
<number box="[698,711,937,961]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
), or with craspedate lobes bearing microtrichia; II–VIII with median pair of setae well developed, arising close together (Figs 
<number box="[880,938,973,997]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.17">2, 17</number>
, 
<number box="[950,981,973,997]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="19.0">19</number>
); sternites sometimes bearing few discal setae. Male usually with oval or transverse pore plates on abdominal sternites (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1141,1009,1033]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 58" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1415,198,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,195,1807]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 58. Brazilian Heterothrips. H. flavitibia female 50 – 52: 50. Dorsal view; 51. Antenna; 52. Abdominal tergites VI – VIII. H. angusticipeps 53 – 54: 53. Female antennal segment III – IV; 54. Male abdominal sternites VII – VIII pore plates. H. peixotoa female 55 – 58: 55. Fore wing; 56. Head; 57. Antenna; 58. Dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280417/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs 
<number box="[1111,1141,1009,1033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="54.67">54</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1154,1185,1009,1033]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 67" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1567,1590]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,192,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[154,1439,192,1547]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 67. Brazilian Heterothrips. H. albipennis sp. n. female 59 – 66: 59. Head; 60. Pronotum; 61. Mesonotum and metanotum; 62. Antenna; 63. Antennal segment III – IV; 64. Fore wing; 65. Abdominal tergites V – VI; 66. Hind leg. H. albipennis sp. n. male: 67. Abdominal sternites VI – VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280418/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">67</figureCitation>
); some species with a pair of dorsolateral finger-like projections on tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[784,871,1045,1069]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 81" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1605,1628]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1583]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1584]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 81. Brazilian Heterothrips. H. paulistarum sp. n. female 73, 75 – 80: 73. Dorsal view; 75. Antenna; 76. Antennal segments III – IV; 77. Head; 78. Pronotum; 79. Abdominal sternites II – VI; 80. Mesonotum and metanotum. H. paulistarum sp. n. male 74, 81: 74. Dorsal view; 81. Abdominal tergites IX – X." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280420/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs 
<number box="[841,871,1045,1069]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="81.107">81</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[883,929,1045,1069]" captionStart="FIGURES 102 – 109" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1868,1891]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,195,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,195,1847]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 102 – 109. Brazilian Heterothrips. H. bicolor female 102, 104 – 106: 102. Dorsal view; 104. Antenna; 105. Pronotum; 106. Mesonotum and metanotum. H. bicolor male 103, 107: 103. Dorsal view; 107. Abdominal tergites IX – X. H. decoratus female 108 - 109: 108. Dorsal view; 109. Abdominal tergites I – VI." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/280423/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">107</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
